Meet up with family, friends and like-minded art lovers at the 10th Hermanus FynArts Festival from 10 â€“ 19 June. Relax, discover, be stimulated and challenged at this 10-day fusion of arts festival and winter school. The programme includes performances, workshops, culinary demonstrations, the Strauss & Co Series of Interviews and Presentations, group and solo art exhibitions, as well as food and wine tastings. The arts festival comprises performances ranging from jazz, music ensembles, duos and trios to choir, dance and theatre and five large-group exhibitions that include ceramics, painting, sculpture and art of thread. In addition, most of the 23 galleries in Hermanus, most within walking distance of each other, will present a special exhibition during the festival. The winter school component is made up of panel discussions, interviews and presentations on a wide range of topics, from the arts to current affairs, fashion and much more. The workshop series include painting techniques ceramics, photography, musical performance, the art of re-using fabric to make string and string products and sculpting wild-life in clay and baking. There are also two 2-day workshops, one on Mindfulness and the second on Creativity. For more information visit www.hermanusfynarts.co.za